ation.","Disconnect the side stand switch electrical connector from the main harness and feed it down to the side stand switch.","Side stand switch electrical connector","Remove the left and right hand frame cradles (see ","Cradle Assemblies - Removal",").","Remove the exhaust system (see ","Exhaust Intermediate and Header Pipes - Removal",")","Disconnect the clutch cable from the crankcase (see ","Clutch Cable - Removal",").","Remove the fixings securing the front sprocket cover to the crankcase.","Front sprocket cover","Fixings","Carefully remove the swinging arm pivot cover on the left hand side of the frame.","Remove the swinging arm pivot nut and collect the washer on the right hand side of the frame.","Nut","Washer","Support the swinging arm and remove the swinging arm spindle and washer from the left hand side.","Partially fit the swinging arm spindle on the right hand side to support the swinging arm. ","Engage ","service tool T3880104"," in the slots of the frame adjuster sleeve and rotate anticlockwise to fully loosen the frame adjuster.","Frame adjuster","T3880104 - Swinging Arm Adjuster Wrench","Remove and discard the fixing and detach the rear brake fluid reservoir from the relay bracket.","Fixing","Brake fluid reservoir","Note the routing of the brake switch harness for installation.","Remove the fixing and detach the ABS brake line P-clip from the lower crankcase.","Fixing","P-clip","ABS brake line","Do not allow a brake component to hang unsupported on the brake hose or line.","Brake hoses or lines that are not supported may become damaged or bent.","Bent or damaged brake hoses or lines lead to reduced braking efficiency causing loss of motorcycle control and an accident.","Remove the fixings and detach the right hand control plate and rear brake master cylinder assembly.","Fixings","Control plate","It is not necessary to disconnect the brake lines to temporarily reposition the rear master cylinder assembly.","Position the control plate and master cylinder assembly rearwards, away from the frame.","Disconnect the oil pressure switch electrical connector.","Loosen the drive chain and remove it from the front sprocket (see ","Final Drive Chain Adjustment",").","From the right hand side, disconnect the following electrical connectors:","Gear position sensor.","Alternator stator.","Crankshaft position sensor.","Starter motor cable to starter solenoid fixing.","Gear position sensor multiplug","Alternator multiplug","Crankshaft position sensor multiplug","Starter motor solenoid","Noting their orientation route the cables away from the frame.","From the left hand side, disconnect the engine earth strap.","Disconnect the crankcase breather hose.","Hose clips","Engine breather pipe","Remove the throttle body and inlet manifold (see ","Throttle Body and Inlet Manifold Assembly - Removal",").","Drain the engine oil (see ","Engine Oil and Filter Renew",").","Drain the coolant (see ","Coolant Replacement - Drainage",").","Remove the radiator (see page ","Radiator - Removal",").","Detach the coolant top hose from the thermostat housing.","Place a support beneath the engine and ensure that the frame is still adequately and securely supported.","Release the engine mounting nuts. Collect the nuts and washers, leaving the bolts in position.","Remove the left hand cylinder head mounting bolt.","Using ","service tool T3880377"," release the:","Rear cylinder head mounting adjuster on the left side of the frame,","Upper rear crankcase mounting adjuster,","Lower rear crankcase mounting adjuster,","Left hand cylinder head mounting adjuster.","Remove the right hand cylinder head mounting bolt.","Remove the remaining mounting bolts, collecting the spacer from the lower crankcase mounting bolt.","Two brake lines are attached to the brake line tidy on the rear of the crankcase.","Failure to detach the brake lines from the brake line tidy will cause damage to the braking system.","Detach the brake lines from the brake line tidy and position away from the crankcase.","Brake line from ABS modulator to front master cylinder","Brake line from ABS modulator to front brake caliper","Brake line tidy","Lower the engine away from the frame, taking care to avoid damage to the brake pipes.","Depending on the type of retaining clip used to hold the ABS brake line, the brake line may detach from the retaining clips during engine removal/install.","A cable tie may be required to hold the ABS brake line in position when installing the engine.","When the engine has been removed, check to ensure that the brake line is attached to the ABS modulator bracket as shown in the following illustration. If required, use a cable tie to secure the brake line to the frame as shown below.","ABS brake line","Retaining clips (require cable tie)","Retaining clips (do not require cable tie)"],"viewCount":0,"infoType":"InfoType05","createdAt":"2024-06-10T12:25:17.579Z","updatedAt":"2024-06-10T12:25:17.579Z","__v":0}